TS13 Whole mouse Showing Only Groups


Second column indicates the path's group status.

' ' : Term is not a group nor is it contained in a group.
'G' : Term is a group.
'>' : Term is directly contained in a group term.
'~' : Term is indirectly contained in a group term.

TS14 Whole mouse Showing Only Groups


Second column indicates the path's group status.

' ' : Term is not a group nor is it contained in a group.
'G' : Term is a group.
'>' : Term is directly contained in a group term.
'~' : Term is indirectly contained in a group term.

TS15 Whole mouse Showing Only Groups


Second column indicates the path's group status.

' ' : Term is not a group nor is it contained in a group.
'G' : Term is a group.
'>' : Term is directly contained in a group term.
'~' : Term is indirectly contained in a group term.

TS16 Whole mouse Showing Only Groups


Second column indicates the path's group status.

' ' : Term is not a group nor is it contained in a group.
'G' : Term is a group.
'>' : Term is directly contained in a group term.
'~' : Term is indirectly contained in a group term.

EMAP:25781   mouse
EMAP:1461  G + embryo
EMAP:1462  > | + branchial arch
EMAP:1463  ~ | | + 1st branchial arch
EMAP:32046 ~ | | | + 1st branchial arch ectoderm
EMAP:34910 ~ | | | + 1st branchial arch endoderm
EMAP:1471  ~ | | | + 1st branchial arch mandibular component
EMAP:1472  ~ | | | | + mandibular component ectoderm
EMAP:1473  ~ | | | | + mandibular component endoderm

TS17 Whole mouse Showing Only Groups


Second column indicates the path's group status.

' ' : Term is not a group nor is it contained in a group.
'G' : Term is a group.
'>' : Term is directly contained in a group term.
'~' : Term is indirectly contained in a group term.

TS18 Whole mouse Showing Only Groups


Second column indicates the path's group status.

' ' : Term is not a group nor is it contained in a group.
'G' : Term is a group.
'>' : Term is directly contained in a group term.
'~' : Term is indirectly contained in a group term.

TS20 Whole mouse Showing Only Groups


Second column indicates the path's group status.

' ' : Term is not a group nor is it contained in a group.
'G' : Term is a group.
'>' : Term is directly contained in a group term.
'~' : Term is indirectly contained in a group term.

TS21 Whole mouse Showing Only Groups


Second column indicates the path's group status.

' ' : Term is not a group nor is it contained in a group.
'G' : Term is a group.
'>' : Term is directly contained in a group term.
'~' : Term is indirectly contained in a group term.

TS22 Whole mouse Showing Only Groups


Second column indicates the path's group status.

' ' : Term is not a group nor is it contained in a group.
'G' : Term is a group.
'>' : Term is directly contained in a group term.
'~' : Term is indirectly contained in a group term.

TS23 Whole mouse Showing Only Groups


Second column indicates the path's group status.

' ' : Term is not a group nor is it contained in a group.
'G' : Term is a group.
'>' : Term is directly contained in a group term.
'~' : Term is indirectly contained in a group term.

TS24 Whole mouse Showing Only Groups


Second column indicates the path's group status.

' ' : Term is not a group nor is it contained in a group.
'G' : Term is a group.
'>' : Term is directly contained in a group term.
'~' : Term is indirectly contained in a group term.

Second column indicates the path's group status.

' ' : Term is not a group nor is it contained in a group.
'G' : Term is a group.
'>' : Term is directly contained in a group term.
'~' : Term is indirectly contained in a group term.

Second column indicates the path's group status.

' ' : Term is not a group nor is it contained in a group.
'G' : Term is a group.
'>' : Term is directly contained in a group term.
'~' : Term is indirectly contained in a group term.

TS27 Whole mouse Showing Only Groups


Second column indicates the path's group status.

' ' : Term is not a group nor is it contained in a group.
'G' : Term is a group.
'>' : Term is directly contained in a group term.
'~' : Term is indirectly contained in a group term.

' ' : Term is not a group nor is it contained in a group.
'G' : Term is a group.
'>' : Term is directly contained in a group term.
'~' : Term is indirectly contained in a group term.
